description: Manchester City Football Club is an English football club from Manchester, founded in 1880 as West Gorton Saint Marks. In 1887 the name was changed to Ardwick Football Club and in 1894 it adopted its current name. The club plays its home games at the Etihad Stadium, in East Manchester. It won the UEFA Champions League for the first time in club history in 2023. The UEFA Super Cup and FIFA Club World Cup were also won that season, making the international treble a reality.
